## 🐛 Bug Report

I am creating xlsx file using new Excel.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter. When adding new worksheet with columns definitions including styles with numFmt defined, that property is not taken into accout and my data is stored with default representation which comes from my database.

Lib version: 4.2.1

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
        const workbook = new Excel.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter({
            stream: anyStream,
            useStyles: true
        }

        const worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('Data', {
            views: [
                { state: 'frozen', ySplit: 1, activeCell: 'A2' }
            ]
        });
        
        worksheet.columns = [
           {
                header: 'Header,
                key: 'header,
                style: {
                    alignment: {
                        horizontal: _.get(column, 'horizontalAlignment', 'left'),
                        vertical: 'middle'
                    },
                    numFmt: '0.00%'
                }
           }
        ]
        
        // then
        worksheet.addRow({ header: 12 });
```

Using code above I can produce excel file with 12 value.

## The expected behaviour:

I expect that code above produce excel file with number formatted to 12.0% representation.

comments.body:
@Noitidart if it's still relevant to you, I ran into this very issue today and after digging a little into the ExcelJS source code, I found out it's a simple matter of adding `useStyles: true` to your `WorkbookWriter` options:

```typescript
    const workbook = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter({
      stream: res,
      useStyles: true,
    })
```
